          <p class="card-title"> Thoracic Spine SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Foam-roller or Tennis balls </p>
          <p class="directions"> Keeping the arms crossed, roll over the device to massage the muscles along your spine - from your neck to mid-back. </p>
          <p class="directions"> For safety, avoid rolling out the lower-back as this has little benefits and can aggravate pre-existing problems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img src="images/smr/theracane-serratus-posterior-release-1.jpg">
          <img src="images/smr/SMR Trapezius.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Middle Trapezius SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Theracane or Tennis/Lacrosse ball</p>
          <p class="directions"> Place a ball between your back and a flat, solid wall. Position it just above one of your shoulder blades and lean back into it.</p>
          <p class="directions"> Roll the ball circularly, seeking out any sore points or muscular tension. </p>
        </div>
